+# Why CVE-2021-26539 Is a False Positive for sanitize-html v1.4.2
+
+This document explains why **CVE-2021-26539** is a **false positive** when reported against **sanitize-html v1.4.2**, and confirms that no patching is required because the vulnerable feature **does not exist** in this version.
+
+---
+
+## 📑 Table of Contents
+
+- [Overview: What Is sanitize-html?](#-overview-what-is-sanitize-html)
+
+- [Why CVE-2021-26539 Is Reported](#-why-cve-2021-26539-is-reported)
+
+- [Why This Version Is NOT Vulnerable](#-why-this-version-is-not-vulnerable)
+
+- [Source Code Analysis and Proof](#-source-code-analysis-and-proof)
+
+- [Why This Is a False Positive](#-why-this-is-a-false-positive)
+
+- [Why You Must NOT Patch This](#-why-you-must-not-patch-this)
+
+- [Recommendations](#-recommendations)
+
+- [Summary](#-summary)
+
+- [References](#-references)
+
+---
+
+## 📌 Overview: What Is sanitize-html?
+
+sanitize-html is a popular npm package that provides HTML sanitization capabilities. It is commonly used to:
+
+- Clean up user-submitted HTML content
+
+- Preserve whitelisted elements and attributes
+
+- Prevent XSS (Cross-Site Scripting) attacks
+
+- Filter out dangerous tags, attributes, and URLs
+
+Because sanitize-html handles **untrusted user input**, it is frequently flagged by security scanners as a critical component requiring vulnerability assessment.
+
+---
+
+## ⚠️ Why CVE-2021-26539 Is Reported
+
+Security scanners report **CVE-2021-26539** based on:
+
+- Static vulnerability metadata from NVD and security advisories
+
+- Package name and version-based matching rules
+
+- Advisory data stating "versions before 2.3.1 are vulnerable"
+
+- Coarse-grained version range matching without feature analysis
+
+As a result, scanners flag **sanitize-html v1.4.2** without verifying whether the **vulnerable feature actually exists** in this version.
+
+---
+
+## ✅ Why This Version Is NOT Vulnerable
+
+The vulnerability described in **CVE-2021-26539** is **not applicable** to sanitize-html v1.4.2.
+
+Key facts:
+
+- CVE-2021-26539 is a vulnerability in the `allowedIframeHostnames` feature
+
+- This feature allows specifying which hostnames are permitted for iframe src attributes
+
+- The vulnerability involves improper handling of Internationalized Domain Names (IDN)
+
+- **The `allowedIframeHostnames` feature does NOT exist in version 1.4.2**
+
+- This feature was introduced in a **later version** of sanitize-html
+
+- You cannot exploit a vulnerability in code that doesn't exist
+
+**Conclusion:**  
+
+Version 1.4.2 is **not affected** by CVE-2021-26539, and no remediation is required.
+
+---
+
+## 🔍 Source Code Analysis and Proof
+
+### 🔹 Vulnerability Details
+
+| Attribute | Value |
+|-----------|-------|
+| CVE ID | CVE-2021-26539 |
+| CVSS v3 Score | 5.3 (MEDIUM) |
+| CWE | CWE-20 (Improper Input Validation) |
+| Affected Feature | `allowedIframeHostnames` option |
+| Attack Vector | IDN homograph attack to bypass hostname whitelist |
+
+### 🔹 Vulnerability Description
+
+CVE-2021-26539 is an improper input validation flaw in sanitize-html related to handling Internationalized Domain Names (IDN) when checking iframe hostnames. The bug allows bypassing the `allowedIframeHostnames` whitelist, potentially letting untrusted iframe sources load despite hostname restrictions.
+
+### 🔹 Source Code Verification
+
+A comprehensive search was performed on the sanitize-html v1.4.2 source code:
+
+| Search Term | Result |
+|-------------|--------|
+| `allowedIframeHostnames` | ❌ NOT FOUND |
+| `iframe` | ❌ NOT FOUND |
+| `IDN` | ❌ NOT FOUND |
+| `hostname` | ❌ NOT FOUND |
+| `punycode` | ❌ NOT FOUND |
+
+### 🔹 Available Options in v1.4.2
+
+The `sanitizeHtml.defaults` object in version 1.4.2 only contains:
+
+```javascript
+sanitizeHtml.defaults = {
+  allowedTags: [ 'h3', 'h4', 'h5', 'h6', 'blockquote', 'p', 'a', 'ul', 'ol', 'nl', 'li', 'b', 'i', 'strong', 'em', 'strike', 'code', 'hr', 'br', 'div', 'table', 'thead', 'caption', 'tbody', 'tr', 'th', 'td', 'pre' ],
+  allowedAttributes: {
+    a: [ 'href', 'name', 'target' ],
+    img: [ 'src' ]
+  },
+  selfClosing: [ 'img', 'br', 'hr', 'area', 'base', 'basefont', 'input', 'link', 'meta' ],
+  allowedSchemes: [ 'http', 'https', 'ftp', 'mailto' ]
+};
+```
+
+**Note:** There is no `allowedIframeHostnames` option or any iframe-related functionality.
+
+### 🔹 Feature Timeline
+
+| Version | Feature Status |
+|---------|---------------|
+| v1.4.2 (Current) | `allowedIframeHostnames` does NOT exist |
+| v1.20.0+ | `allowedIframeHostnames` feature introduced |
+| v2.3.1 | IDN bypass vulnerability fixed |
+
+This confirms that the vulnerable code path **does not exist** in version 1.4.2.
+
+---
+
+## ❗ Why This Is a False Positive
+
+This finding is a **false positive** because:
+
+- The scanner uses **coarse-grained version matching** (< 2.3.1)
+
+- Feature presence is not evaluated in vulnerability assessment
+
+- The `allowedIframeHostnames` feature was added AFTER version 1.4.2
+
+- Version 1.4.2 predates the introduction of the vulnerable feature
+
+- **You cannot have a vulnerability in code that doesn't exist**
+
+The report reflects a **tooling limitation**, not a real vulnerability.
+
+---
+
+## 💥 Why You Must NOT Patch This
+
+Attempting to patch sanitize-html v1.4.2 for CVE-2021-26539 is **incorrect and unnecessary**:
+
+- ✅ The vulnerable feature does not exist in this version
+
+- ❌ There is no code to patch
+
+- ❌ Applying a "fix" for non-existent code makes no sense
+
+- ❌ Manual modifications would only add unnecessary complexity
+
+- ❌ The IDN hostname validation logic simply isn't present
+
+There is **nothing to patch**.
+
+---
+
+## ✅ Recommendations
+
+- ✅ Mark **CVE-2021-26539** as **FALSE POSITIVE** for v1.4.2
+
+- ✅ Do not apply any patches or backports
+
+- ✅ Continue using sanitize-html v1.4.2 if it meets your requirements
+
+- 📝 Document this justification for audit purposes
+
+- 🔄 Continue standard dependency monitoring
+
+- ⚠️ Note: If you need the `allowedIframeHostnames` feature, you must upgrade to v2.3.2 or later
+
+---
+
+## 🧷 Summary
+
